contentrichtext.text: '''Louis Napoleon''' may refer to: * [[Louis Bonaparte]] or Louis Napoléon Bonaparte, (1778–1846), King Louis I of Holland, brother of Napoleon I * [[Napoléon Louis Bonaparte]] (1804–1831), King Louis II of Holland, second son of Louis Bonaparte (1778–1846) * [[Napoléon III]] (1808–1873), usually called Louis Napoléon, President and later Emperor of the French, third son of Louis Bonaparte * [[Napoléon Eugène, Prince Imperial]] or Napoléon IV, Prince Imperial, often referred to as Louis Napoléon (1856–1879), only child of Napoleon III * [[Prince Louis Napoléon]] or Napoléon VI, Prince Imperial, (1914–1997), pretender to the French throne {{hndis}} [[de:Louis Napoléon]]
